  <brief_title>The Effect of Coenzyme Q10 on Hearing and Tinnitus Characteristics of Chronic Tinnitus Patients</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>University Hospital, Antwerp</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>University Hospital, Antwerp</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is a randomised double-blinded trial. A group of 40 tinnitus patients with a
      naturally low Q10 level will be selected out of a preselected group of 160 screened out of a
      pre-existed database or patients which visited the ENT-consultation. The 40 patients with the
      lowest level will be asked to take 2 months Q10 (n=20) or the placebo (n=20). To evaluate the
      effect on hearing and tinnitus characteristic; audiometric test, tinnitus analysis and
      auditory evoked responses will be used as outcome measurements.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
